    "Body": " Principal Architect - Cryptography and Blockchain at Salesforce.com, Inc San Francisco, CA 94199 ? About the Job Job Category Products and Technology Job Details Security is our #1 priority. \"Nothing is more important than the security of our service and customer data.\" The Salesforce Blockchain Team is seeking an experienced enterprise security and Crypto pioneer . Enterprise security is critical to the success of Salesforce, Business Technology, and Salesforce employees. As the Security Architect of this team, you will strategically influence, define, design and implement the present and future of how we secure our Blockchain Key Store and build a truly de-centralized Infrastructure in balance with the usability needs of our customers and partners. A successful candidate will own the roadmap for the full spectrum of enterprise security controls, assets, and engineering enablement and will drive that vision with the help of our trusted partners in Business Technology. Primary Responsibilities: Applied Cryptographer with full stack development. Experience with PKI, X509, OWASP, PKCS#11,HSM Experience building Multi-Factor Authentication Security and privacy primitives including understanding of cryptography concepts. Hands-on usage of crypto libraries such as OpenSSL, mbedTLS. Storage protocols such as NVMe, SATA. Background in working with FPGAs for prototyping Prototype new features that will enable and secure both real-time and non-realtime peer-to-peer communication over heterogeneous networks. Follow trends in technology and apply new security approaches for device-identity, authentication, attestation, key-storage, and management. Document software designs, functional and design specifications, presentations, and other documents as needed Consensus and consistency frameworks (e.g., POET, Raft, eventual consistency) Participate in all phases of the software development life cycle from design to development to deployment. Drive Enterprise Security initiatives in relation to securing assets, customer services delivery, and regulatory/audit compliance. Hands-on experience with container technologies (e.g., Docker, Kubernetes) Required Qualifications: Ph.D. or Masters in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, or equivalent 10+ years of hand-on experience working in a security-focused role in the technology or other technology-heavy industry. 5+ years experience in development of cryptography, blockchain, PKI and similar areas. In-depth knowledge of common application and infrastructure security vulnerabilities and mitigations Experience with cloud computing architectures and the associated security designs and challenges Skilled in implementing secure modern Identity and Access Management (IAM) Experience in implementing mail security capabilities (DMARC, SPF and DKIM) Experience implementing zero trust security models such as BeyondCorp Experience implementing SDLC process, technology, and automation Experience with common open source libraries and technologies ) and how to effectively harden them Experience with common web application development technologies (e.g. Java, PHP, Python, AJAX, etc...) along with tools and processes to enable teams to develop safely Strong cross-functional leadership and team building skills Experience engaging with customers regarding security Excellent verbal and written communication skills Salesforce, the Customer Success Platform and world's #1 CRM, empowers companies to connect with their customers in a whole new way. We are the fastest growing of the top 10 enterprise software companies, the Worlds Most Innovative Company according to Forbes, and one of Fortunes 100 Best Companies to Work For six years running. The growth, innovation, and Aloha spirit of Salesforce are driven by our incredible employees who thrive on delivering success for our customers while also finding time to give back through our 1/1/1 model, which leverages 1% of our time, equity, and product to improve communities around the world. Salesforce is a team sport, and we play to win. Join us! *LI-Y Accessibility - If you require accessibility assistance applying for open positions please contact the Salesforce.com Recruiting Department at mailto:applicant_access@salesforce.com . Posting Statement Salesforce.com and Salesforce.org are Equal Employment Opportunity and Affirmative Action Employers. Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender perception or identity, national origin, age, marital status, protected veteran status, or disability status. Headhunters and recruitment agencies may not submit resumes/CVs through this Web site or directly to managers. Salesforce.com and Salesforce.org do not accept unsolicited headhunter and agency resumes. Salesforce.com and Salesforce.org will not pay fees to any third-party agency or company that does not have a signed agreement with Salesforce.com or Salesforce.org. Pursuant to the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance and the Los Angeles Fair Chance Initiative for Hiring, Salesforce will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records. Founded in 1999, Salesforce is the global leader in Customer Relationship Management (CRM). Companies of every size and industry are using Salesforce to transform their businesses, across sales, service, marketing, commerce, and more by connecting with customers in a whole new way. We harness technologies that can revolutionize companies, careers, and, hopefully, our world. Salesforce is built on a set of four core values: Trust, Customer Success, Innovation, and Equality. By making technology more accessible, we're helping create a future with greater opportunity and equality for all. This has taken our company to great heights, including being ranked by Fortune as one of the Most Admired Companies in the World and one of the 100 Best Companies to Work For eleven years in a row, and named Innovator of the Decade and one of the Worlds Most Innovative Companies eight years in a row by Forbes. There are those who choose to work with the best and brightest. And then, there are those who want to do more than just a job. They are the ones improving lives, not only their careers. Having an impact now instead of later. Doing something thats so much bigger than themselves, an industry, and their company. We believe everyone can be a Trailblazer. Join Salesforce and discover a future of new opportunities. ", 
